✅ 1. Triangle Number Pattern using Nested Loops

📌 Program

public class NumberPattern {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        int n = 5;

        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {

                // Conditional check
                if (j % 2 == 0) {
                    System.out.print("* ");
                } else {
                    System.out.print(j + " ");
                }
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}


⸻

✅ Output

1
1 *
1 * 3
1 * 3 *
1 * 3 * 5


⸻

🧠 Conclusion

This program uses nested loops to generate a triangle pattern and applies conditional statements to print numbers and symbols based on conditions.

